My own great grandparents were married when my great grandfather was
31 and his bride was 14. She and her sister married brothers from the
same home town in France. The brothers had come to the US several
years prior to the wedding, the sisters only some months prior.
Whether it was the brides' or the grooms' family who instigated the
pretty obviously arranged marriages, we don't know. Would it make a
difference in terms of them being seen as an &quot;acceptably normal
situation&quot;? Was there &quot;talk?&quot; Not that we're aware of (and there's
been a good deal of family research into the lives of these people).
